would go to sleep...

76
00:06:26,058 --> 00:06:31,587
on a foldable beach chair
out of sight...

77
00:06:31,798 --> 00:06:33,561
and the lobby would then
be deserted.

78
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:36,600
You say it with such fondness!

79
00:06:40,741 --> 00:06:42,971
Look, it wasn't all that good.

80
00:06:43,176 --> 00:06:46,840
Only when we were having fun,
but things could turn sour.

81
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:51,779
First, some woman would show up,
throwing a fit.

82
00:06:52,186 --> 00:06:55,486
Then someone else,
waving a pocketknife.

83
00:06:55,691 --> 00:06:59,218
It'd go on like this.

84
00:06:59,428 --> 00:07:02,693
So the cops were called.

85
00:07:02,898 --> 00:07:08,565
When fights broke out,
the cops would come, and go up.

86
00:07:08,772 --> 00:07:11,935
Out front, there was a scaffold,
for the facade was being painted.

87
00:07:12,142 --> 00:07:16,841
So someone would rappel down
the scaffold ropes.

88
00:07:22,887 --> 00:07:25,913
Then, a second person
would rappel down...

89
00:07:26,123 --> 00:07:29,787
from the 7th or 8th floor.

90
00:07:29,995 --> 00:07:33,294
Then a third one. I'd say:
"What the hell is this?"

91
00:07:33,498 --> 00:07:38,435
all night long...
In the morning I'd say:

92
00:07:38,637 --> 00:07:41,402
"Who's giving the scoop
of what happened...

93
00:07:41,607 --> 00:07:46,135
you or me, Conceição?
About what we saw last night?"

94
00:07:46,346 --> 00:07:51,181
We'd give each other the scoop,
saying it was a news flash.

95
00:07:51,551 --> 00:07:56,888
Before Sergio, this was hell,
but thank God, all's calm now.

96
00:07:57,491 --> 00:08:00,483
all's great,
but the poor fellow suffered...

97
00:08:00,694 --> 00:08:03,185
to chase out of here
the transvestites...

98
00:08:03,397 --> 00:08:06,856
prostitution, the massage parlors.

99
00:08:07,068 --> 00:08:11,437
Good Lord! He kept going
down to the district...

100
00:08:11,639 --> 00:08:15,075
the poor guy suffered.
We would go testify...

101
00:08:15,276 --> 00:08:20,840
and so would the doormen.
Now it's better. all's fine.

102
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,802
We're here.
This is our crew.

103
00:08:45,143 --> 00:08:47,111
I'll see myself in, okay?

104
00:08:47,311 --> 00:08:50,372
How are you?
This is Jacques.

105
00:08:50,582 --> 00:08:53,016
This is Coutinho, the director.

106
00:08:53,218 --> 00:08:56,745
- You look smart, huh?
- Yeah, but one should look smart?

107
00:08:56,955 --> 00:08:59,719
My favorite objects?
My portraits!

108
00:09:00,826 --> 00:09:02,385
Definitely!

109
00:09:02,595 --> 00:09:06,554
- Tell me why.
- Cause I love myself.

110
00:09:06,766 --> 00:09:09,860
We should all love
ourselves, right?

111
00:09:10,069 --> 00:09:12,731
If I don't love myself,
who will?

112
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:15,235
Except when you have a boyfriend.

113
00:09:15,443 --> 00:09:18,537
Then you love your boyfriend,
of course!

114
00:09:19,547 --> 00:09:23,074
I began posing for portraits
after my divorce.

115
00:09:23,451 --> 00:09:26,785
I started working as a seamstress
for the high society.

116
00:09:26,988 --> 00:09:29,354
I worked for
Roberto Marinho's famlly...

117
00:09:29,558 --> 00:09:33,722
Othon Palace Hotel's ,
and Niemeyer's family.

118
00:09:33,929 --> 00:09:38,458
I had to polish my act.

119
00:09:38,668 --> 00:09:42,434
I learned many great things
with the high society.

120
00:09:42,638 --> 00:09:47,268
Then I started posing for portraits,
cause I fell in love with myself.

121
00:09:47,477 --> 00:09:52,973
And to this day, I've got portraits
on my phones and about everywhere!

122
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:57,152
We live in one of Rio's
postcards: Copacabana.

123
00:09:57,921 --> 00:10:01,016
It's very violent here, though.

124
00:10:01,226 --> 00:10:03,922
How was your mugging,
Ms. Esther?

125
00:10:04,128 --> 00:10:05,186
- Here?
- Yeah.

126
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:11,666
I was on Siqueira Campos St.,
near here...

127
00:10:11,871 --> 00:10:14,567
when a guy and a woman
approached me.

128
00:10:14,773 --> 00:10:19,142
I got quite frightened.
Then...

129
00:10:19,345 --> 00:10:20,744
he took his piece out of
his pocket.

130
00:10:20,946 --> 00:10:23,347
When I saw the gun,
I panicked.

131
00:10:23,950 --> 00:10:27,852
He said: "Be quiet,
and don't look sideways."

132
00:10:28,588 --> 00:10:30,351
"Where do you live?"

133
00:10:30,557 --> 00:10:34,517
When I came in here,
I got so scared...

134
00:10:34,729 --> 00:10:37,357
really scared of him.

135
00:10:37,565 --> 00:10:40,398
Such a handsome man! White...

136
00:10:40,601 --> 00:10:43,798
really well- dressed.

137
00:10:44,005 --> 00:10:48,705
He said:
"Where's your bank card?"

138
00:10:49,444 --> 00:10:53,778
I said: "I don't know!"I shook
so badly, I was speechless!

139
00:10:53,982 --> 00:10:57,419
I opened up a drawer,
emptied it on my bed...

140
00:10:57,620 --> 00:11:00,384
kneeling on the floor, looking
for it, but couldn't find it...

141
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:03,024
being under gunpoint like that.

142
00:11:03,226 --> 00:11:05,285
I had to crawl on my knees...

143
00:11:05,495 --> 00:11:10,399
grab his leg,
and beg him not to shoot me.

144
00:11:10,601 --> 00:11:13,798
Then we left for the bank.

145
00:11:15,072 --> 00:11:18,235
He cashed all my money,
R$ 8,OOO reais.

146
00:11:19,476 --> 00:11:22,878
He had the gun on me all the time.

147
00:11:23,214 --> 00:11:29,449
I think the branch manager
was in it with him...

148
00:11:29,654 --> 00:11:34,752
cause he paid right up. For you
to cash a couple thousand reais...

149
00:11:34,961 --> 00:11:37,156
a 24- hour notice is required.

150
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:40,821
I came back home,
in such a state!

151
00:11:41,601 --> 00:11:44,162
I couldn't stop crying.

152
00:11:44,905 --> 00:11:49,399
He handed me a damn bag
that's still here!

153
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:51,339
It's here, that damn bag!

154
00:11:52,512 --> 00:11:55,107
He said: "Keep it.
I don't need your money."

155
00:11:55,316 --> 00:11:58,774
I thought the money
was really there.

156
00:11:58,987 --> 00:12:02,184
Boy, what a letdown!

157
00:12:02,657 --> 00:12:04,454
The bag's here.

158
00:12:06,027 --> 00:12:08,997
Here's the damn bag.

159
00:12:09,465 --> 00:12:12,525
I find it disgusting.

160
00:12:12,735 --> 00:12:16,000
Look, he did all this!

161
00:12:17,039 --> 00:12:19,201
It's disgusting.

162
00:12:22,712 --> 00:12:26,876
all nicely folded up,
so I'd take it for my money.

163
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:30,311
I got desperate,
when I saw myself alone here...

164
00:12:30,521 --> 00:12:35,515
pacing up and down,
debt- ridden at C&A, and Ponto Frio...

165
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:41,524
At 4 am, I got dressed and decided
to jump out of the window.

166
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:43,758
I was going to jump.

167
00:12:45,203 --> 00:12:50,368
It'd been two years my late
husband had died...

168
00:12:50,575 --> 00:12:53,841
and left me alone.
But I...

169
00:12:54,047 --> 00:13:00,077
didn't go through with it.
People always teased me:

170
00:13:00,286 --> 00:13:03,881
"You didn't jump because of
C&A and Ponto Frio?"

171
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:07,891
I said: "Yes", cause I'm not
like those who say:

172
00:13:08,095 --> 00:13:10,563
"The dead don't have to honor
their debts."

173
00:13:10,764 --> 00:13:13,494
When I die,
I want to go in peace!

174
00:13:13,701 --> 00:13:16,068
Not owing a dime to anyone.

175
00:13:16,271 --> 00:13:20,799
Now I have a really
great boyfriend.

176
00:13:21,009 --> 00:13:25,412
I'm very happy.
One shouldn't be alone.

177
00:13:25,613 --> 00:13:29,846
We should all have someone.
I'm not dead yet.

178
00:13:30,052 --> 00:13:35,615
Men and women need companions,
don't you think so?

179
00:13:35,825 --> 00:13:37,850
We all need a partner.

180
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:40,621
You spend your daytime with
your friends, and that's nice.

181
00:13:40,831 --> 00:13:44,198
Then you come home,
and Iock your front door...

182
00:13:44,401 --> 00:13:46,494
My friends tease me, saying:

183
00:13:46,703 --> 00:13:51,641
"If you dislike being alone within 4
white walls, paint them in colors!"

184
00:13:52,243 --> 00:13:55,474
It's easy for them to say so,
cause they're not in here.

185
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:59,411
Solitude hurts a lot.
It hurts a lot.

